#Small Node.js api
### This is a small node.js api that is able to create user and login if the user does exists.
### So I have used  PostgreSQL as my database, Sequelize to create models and to connect to our express server, 
bcryptjs to hash passwords.


#Technologies used.

*Node.js  —  For writng Javasctipt server-side applications
*Express.js  —  For server.
*PostgreSQL — An open source object-relational database
*Sequelize — An ORM(Object Relational Mapping) of PostreSQL 
*Bcryptjs  —  For password hashing
*Body-parser  —  For getting user imports